        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:06PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 406 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lordstown, or near Warren, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Youngstown, Warren, Boardman, Niles, Campbell, Hubbard, Canfield,
Cortland, Lordstown, Vienna Center, Hilltop, Maplewood Park,
Leavittsburg, Austintown, Struthers, Girard, Vienna, McDonald,
Orangeville, and Yankee Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
